## bootstrap-audit (chassis-shipped, default-on)

Weekly verification of the five known install gaps (see
`chassis/scripts/bootstrap-audit.sh`). Silent on a clean install; fires
Claude only when one or more checks fail. Catches silent regressions -
e.g. an OS update bootouts a LaunchDaemon, a `.mcp.json` edit drops the
memory block, the customer remote gets re-pointed.

```yaml
schedule: weekly sunday 09:00
gather: ${CHASSIS_HOME}/chassis/scripts/gather-bootstrap-audit.sh
condition: threshold count > 0
prompt: ${CHASSIS_HOME}/chassis/scheduled-tasks/bootstrap-audit-prompt.md
model: sonnet
budget: 1
criticality: background
```

---

## chassis-update-check (chassis-shipped, default-on)

Weekly check of `chassis/VERSION` against upstream `scrollinondubs/behalfbot`
main. Silent when up to date or the offered version was already dismissed.
Fires Claude only when a newer chassis is available, at which point Claude
posts a single consent notification to the owner's alerts channel.

Application is gated behind the `update chassis` / `update chassis --force`
Discord trigger (`chassis/skills/chassis-update.md`); this heartbeat NEVER
applies the update itself.

Opt out via `auto_update.check: false` in `chassis.config.yaml`.

Issue: scrollinondubs/behalfbot#33.

```yaml
schedule: weekly monday 09:00
gather: ${CHASSIS_HOME}/chassis/scripts/gather-chassis-update-check.sh
condition: threshold count > 0
prompt: ${CHASSIS_HOME}/chassis/scheduled-tasks/chassis-update-check-prompt.md
model: sonnet
budget: 1
criticality: background
```

